RESUSCITATION BAY (SECTOR A)

97
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,840
How did this happen?

98
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:53,200
Actually, we were so close.

99
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,480
The next time,

100
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:01,640
we need to buy more
time no matter what.

101
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,640
That way, no one gets hurt.

102
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,200
There may not be the next time.

103
00:09:07,680 --> 00:09:09,320
Let's say saving
all the passengers

104
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,320
is the key to breaking
out of the time loop.

105
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,320
Well, we already did that.

106
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,000
This is the last time.

107
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,640
But I can't shake the feeling
that we haven't resolved anything.

108
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,960
I feel like something
more happened

109
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,080
after Wang Mengmeng's death.

110
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,160
Look this up for me.

111
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:39,400
"May 13th, 2014.

112
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,280
River-crossing
bridge car accident.

113
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,240
Route 45."

114
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,520
Look at this.

115
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,600
DO YOU THINK YOU'RE SPECIAL?

116
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,000
SHE SHOULDN'T HAVE BEEN BORN

117
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,280
SHE'S NOT RIGHT IN THE HEAD

118
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,560
SCUM OF SOCIETY

119
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:03,960
DIE!

120
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,720
DOES SHE THINK THE
WORLD OWES HER?

121
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,720
NICE DEATH!

122
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:10,360
SHE MUST'VE BEEN SPOILED ROTTEN

123
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:28,200
If Wang Mengmeng's parents

124
00:10:28,680 --> 00:10:30,200
see these comments,

125
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,840
what will they think?

126
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:36,400
Maybe

127
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:39,080
for them,

128
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:42,160
surviving isn't true salvation.

129
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:51,360
We probably haven't gotten
to the heart of all this yet.

130
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:06,880
TUESDAY, JIALIN
RIVER-CROSSING BRIDGE

131
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:11,600
TUESDAY, JIALIN
RIVER-CROSSING BRIDGE

132
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:14,840
After what happened
to Wang Mengmeng,

133
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:16,800
Wang Xingde and Tao
Yinghong were dissatisfied

134
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,280
with the
investigation's outcome.

135
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:22,120
They also asked the police to investigate
why Wang Mengmeng got off the bus.

136
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,960
Is the involved bus
driver here yet?

137
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:25,960
He should be here soon.

138
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:27,360
I'll receive him at the door.

139
00:11:32,120 --> 00:11:33,120
Mr. Qin.

140
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:35,800
- Ms. Du.
- Thank you for coming, Mr. Qin.

141
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,720
- Did you bring everything?
- Yes, I did.

142
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,960
These are the statements,
accident reports,

143
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,760
and all the related documents.

144
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,480
This case wasn't
that complicated.

145
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,920
There was nothing suspicious.

146
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,760
It was just a traffic accident.

147
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,600
Chain of evidence intact.

148
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:50,880
The cause was clear.

149
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,880
We determined that

150
00:11:51,960 --> 00:11:54,016
the bus driver who let her
out had primary liability.

151
00:11:54,040 --> 00:11:55,600
The dump truck had
secondary liability.

152
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,800
Were there any problems
with compensation?

153
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,040
There were none.

154
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:01,520
The bus company paid
the compensation.

155
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,760
The victim's family
didn't file a lawsuit.

156
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,080
There was no financial dispute.

157
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:10,640
Ms. Du.

158
00:12:12,680 --> 00:12:14,040
He is the one from the case.

159
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:16,000
Mr. Zhu, the driver
of the Route 45 bus.

160
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,640
Mr. Zhu, this is Ms. Du.

161
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,960
Hello, Mr. Zhu.

162
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:20,040
Have a seat.

163
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,360
Come, sit down.

164
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:22,920
- Sit down, Mr. Qin.
- Okay.

165
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,400
Have a seat, Mr. Zhu.

166
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,240
Don't be nervous, Mr. Zhu.

167
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:33,560
We just want to learn more
from you about the situation.

168
00:12:33,640 --> 00:12:35,680
Just tell us the truth.

169
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:38,040
We were watching this video.

170
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,880
Wang Mengmeng was in a hurry
when she got off the bus.

171
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,920
And she had arguments
and tussles with you.

172
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,920
So what happened?

173
00:12:46,920 --> 00:12:49,560
It has already been five years.

174
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:53,200
I've been asked all
the questions before.

175
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,680
You are Mr. Qin

176
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:57,480
from back then, right?

177
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:58,480
Yes, it's me.

178
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:01,520
Then you know better
than anyone else.

179
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,040
You should talk to them.

180
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,520
I answered all the
questions back then.

181
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,360
- All I can do now is...
- Mr. Zhu.

182
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,640
You've heard about the bombing.

183
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,360
This is a serious case.

184
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,520
Please cooperate.

185
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,800
At the time, that young lady

186
00:13:26,280 --> 00:13:27,680
insisted on getting off.

187
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,280
I really didn't expect this

188
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,600
to happen.

189
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:33,240
Otherwise,

190
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:34,960
I wouldn't have let
her off the bus.

191
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:37,640
But under the circumstances,

192
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,760
I had no choice but
to drop her off.

193
00:13:40,560 --> 00:13:43,200
I'm sure you've all seen
the security footage.

194
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,320
At the time,

195
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,880
she was already
pulling on my arm.

196
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:49,480
What if the bus was
steered off course?

197
00:13:49,560 --> 00:13:50,560
What would happen?

198
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:53,160
The consequences
would be even worse.

199
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:54,520
I'm a driver.

200
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:57,920
I have to ensure the safety of
the dozens of passengers on board.

201
00:13:58,400 --> 00:14:00,440
If she had acted up

202
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:01,920
anywhere else,

203
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,120
I could have pulled
over for her.

204
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,800
On the river-crossing bridge,

205
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:08,200
there is no way.

206
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:11,200
Didn't you think of asking
the passengers to stop her?

207
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,480
No one on the bus helped.

208
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:18,520
After the accident, did Wang
Mengmeng's parents contact you?

209
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,920
Did they ask you why
Wang Mengmeng got off?

210
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,320
Nothing in the world

211
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,200
could make me brave enough
to talk to them face-to-face.

212
00:14:26,760 --> 00:14:30,000
I know that even if I were
to kneel and kowtow to them,

213
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,360
they wouldn't accept it either.

214
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:34,160
Especially that lady. She…

215
00:14:35,800 --> 00:14:37,160
Yes, I know.

216
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,920
I breached the protocol.

217
00:14:43,280 --> 00:14:46,400
I know that I lost my
job because of this.

218
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,480
I've admitted it myself.

219
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:54,800
How much do you know
about the real reason

220
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:55,960
that Wang Mengmeng got off?

221
00:14:56,560 --> 00:14:58,120
Or did she say anything to you?

222
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:01,640
That young girl just
missed her stop.

223
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,040
I've seen this

224
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:04,640
more than a few times before.

225
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,880
She kept babbling on and on.

226
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,480
What she said didn't
make any sense.

227
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:09,320
I didn't know what she wanted.

228
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,320
She just kept wanting me
to stop and let her out.

229
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:13,360
I was focused on the road.

230
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:15,200
I didn't know what to do.

231
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:16,680
It's the river-crossing bridge!

232
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,400
You can't stop there!

233
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,520
But you still stopped.

234
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,040
Yes, I know I did stop!

235
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:22,760
But what could I do?

236
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,640
Five years have already passed!

237
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:26,720
Why won't you let it go?

238
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,040
Didn't you call me here
today to interrogate me?

239
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,920
- No.
- Fine. Take me and execute me!

240
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,256
- My life for hers!
- No, Mr. Zhu.

241
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,560
- Mr. Zhu.
- Here.

242
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:34,880
That's not our intention.

243
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,160
Please have a seat.

244
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,480
Mr. Zhu, calm down.

245
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:39,080
Don't get so worked up.

246
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:40,600
That's not our intention.

247
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:41,680
We told you to come

248
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:43,840
just to ask you to
think back carefully.

249
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,920
Did you upset her parents

250
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,600
to make them resent you?

251
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,680
Resent?

252
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:51,760
Who doesn't harbor resentment?

253
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:55,720
I have resentment too.

254
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,720
Okay, Mr. Zhu.

255
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:08,720
Don't get worked up.

256
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,280
Let's take a break.

257
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,480
Here, Xiaoliu.

258
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,400
Take Mr. Zhu to get
some tea and rest.

259
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,840
- Come.
- Mr. Zhu.

260
00:16:14,920 --> 00:16:16,800
Here. Take a break.

261
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,760
- Mrs. Zhang.
- Where is Zhang Cheng?

262
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:34,600
I'm asking you. Where is he?

263
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:44,160
We took a closer look at the
security cameras on the bus.

264
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,160
We also talked to the
passengers on the bus.

265
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,600
No one knows why Wang
Mengmeng got off the bus.

266
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,720
We only found out that

267
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:52,280
she seriously interfered
with the driver's driving.

268
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:54,960
And aside from her frantic
hitting of the bus door,

269
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:57,880
there was no proof that she
was in any physical danger.

